# LAMMPS Input File
# Licensed under CC BY 4.0
# A Set of Materials-Science Tutorials for the LAMMPS Simulation Package
# Modernized recreation of the MSU/CAVS tutorials by Mark A. Tschopp
# Tutorial 15, part 1: bracket the melting point of aluminum from the
# heating/cooling hysteresis of a single-phase crystal.
#
# A bulk fcc crystal is heated through melting and then the melt is cooled
# back down, both at constant pressure.  The volume jumps at melting and
# freezing, but a defect-free crystal SUPERHEATS before it melts and the melt
# SUPERCOOLS before it freezes, so the two branches form a hysteresis loop.
# The true melting point lies inside the loop -- which is why part 2 uses the
# two-phase method to pin it down.

units metal
atom_style atomic
boundary p p p
lattice fcc 4.05
Lattice spacing in x,y,z = 4.05 4.05 4.05
region box block 0 8 0 8 0 8
create_box 1 box
Created orthogonal box = (0 0 0) to (32.4 32.4 32.4)
  1 by 1 by 1 MPI processor grid
create_atoms 1 box
Created 2048 atoms
  using lattice units in orthogonal box = (0 0 0) to (32.4 32.4 32.4)
  create_atoms CPU = 0.001 seconds
mass 1 26.98
pair_style eam/fs
pair_coeff * * Al_mm.eam.fs Al
Reading eam/fs potential file Al_mm.eam.fs with DATE: 2007-06-11
velocity all create 300.0 12345 mom yes rot yes
timestep 0.002
thermo 5000

variable temp equal temp
variable vat  equal vol/atoms

# equilibrate the solid at 300 K and constant (zero) pressure
fix relax all npt temp 300.0 300.0 0.2 iso 0.0 0.0 2.0
run 10000
